---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/PageHero.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy policy"
  description="How Bundle Technologies Ltd collects, uses and protects personal data — plain-English summary first, full UK GDPR detail below."
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Legal"
    title="Privacy policy"
    lead="Last updated: 6 July 2026 · Plain-English summary first, full detail below."
  />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <div class="prose reveal">
        <div class="callout">
          <p><strong>The short version</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>We collect only what we need to run a waitlist and improve this site.</li>
            <li>We never sell your data — to anyone, for anything.</li>
            <li>Waitlist emails are used only for launch updates, nothing else.</li>
            <li>
              You can ask us to delete your data at any time:
              <a href="mailto:privacy@bundle.ai">privacy@bundle.ai</a>.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <h2>Who we are</h2>
        <p>
          Bundle Technologies Ltd (“Bundle”, “we”) is a company registered in
          England and Wales, based in London. We are building an
          education-first platform for startup investing; no investment
          services are live yet, so the personal data we hold is limited to
          what this website collects. For the purposes of the UK GDPR and the
          Data Protection Act 2018, Bundle Technologies Ltd is the controller
          of that data.
        </p>

        <h2>What we collect</h2>
        <p>We deliberately collect very little.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Waitlist details.</strong> Your email address and, if you
            choose to tell us, which best describes you — investor, founder or
            simply curious. That is the whole form, by design.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Analytics-lite.</strong> Aggregate usage data — which pages
            are read, roughly where visitors come from — measured without
            cross-site tracking. We do not use marketing pixels, advertising
            identifiers or fingerprinting.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Correspondence.</strong> If you email us, we keep the
            exchange so we can reply properly and remember the context next
            time.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Legal bases</h2>
        <p>
          Under the UK GDPR we rely on two legal bases. <strong>Consent</strong>,
          when you join the waitlist — you can withdraw it at any time by
          unsubscribing or emailing us, and withdrawing is as easy as joining
          was. <strong>Legitimate interests</strong>, for minimal analytics,
          administering the site and keeping it secure — interests we have
          balanced against your rights and freedoms.
        </p>

        <h2>How long we keep it</h2>
        <p>
          Waitlist data is kept until you unsubscribe or until early-access
          invitations are complete, after which it is deleted or anonymised.
          Correspondence is kept for up to two years after a thread closes. We
          do not keep personal data “just in case”.
        </p>

        <h2>Your rights</h2>
        <p>
          You have the right to access the personal data we hold about you, to
          have it rectified or erased, to receive it in a portable format, and
          to restrict or object to certain processing. One plain email to
          <a href="mailto:privacy@bundle.ai">privacy@bundle.ai</a> is enough —
          no forms. You also have the right to complain to the Information
          Commissioner’s Office (<a href="https://ico.org.uk" rel="noopener">ico.org.uk</a>),
          though we would appreciate the chance to put things right first.
        </p>

        <h2>Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          We use only functional cookies — the kind that remember practical
          things, such as a notice you have dismissed. No advertising cookies,
          no cross-site tracking, no third-party pixels. Because we set no
          non-essential cookies, we do not interrupt you with a consent banner.
        </p>

        <h2>AI and your data</h2>
        <p>
          Bundle is building AI-assisted tools, so it matters to say this
          precisely: where AI features process personal data, they operate
          under human oversight, and we make no automated decisions with legal
          or similarly significant effects about you without human review.
          Waitlist data is not used to train AI models.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions, requests or complaints:
          <a href="mailto:privacy@bundle.ai">privacy@bundle.ai</a>, or write to
          Bundle Technologies Ltd, London, United Kingdom. We aim to respond to
          rights requests well within the one-month statutory window.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .callout > p {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .callout ul {
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
  }
</style>
